headline: Fed rate decision 'puzzling,' market strategist says
summary: STORY: A divided U.S. Federal Reserve cut interest rates by a quarter of a percentage point on Wednesday (October 29), despite dissent from two policy makers."Why in the world are they cutting rates now?" asks Smith. "If you look at the last data that we got, the ADP report and you look at that by sector, you can see that most of the decline in job growth is coming from a couple of sectors," construction, technology and government."That's a trend that's going to continue and is not susceptible to improvement from a 25 basis point rate cut."

headline: Payroll Processors Continue to Slide. What the Charts of Paylocity Holding, Paycom Software Say.
summary: Employment-related news may be sending an early warning that the labor market is losing steam, a precursor to a recession.  Meta Platforms Amazon,  Microsoft Intel Corp United Parcel Service Applied Materials, and Target are just some of the names disclosing job cuts in recent weeks.  Shares of payroll processors, staffing firms, and the like—companies that often lead employment trends—have begun to weaken.

headline: ADP Q3 Deep Dive: Embedded Payroll, AI Initiatives, and Client Hiring Slowdown Shape Outlook
summary: Payroll and HR services provider Automatic Data Processing (NASDAQ:ADP) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 7.1% year on year to $5.18 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $5.33 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.49 per share was 1.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
